NEDPOWER MOUNT STORM, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
NedPower Mount Storm, LLC ("NedPower") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the NedPower generating facility ("NedPower Facility").
The NedPower Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Grant County, West Virginia. The NedPower Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Monongahela Power Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth NedPower's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the NedPower Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
NedPower's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to NedPower shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff . MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $737,500.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $61,458.33.
